snippet.description:

If you have any questions about the brand relating to how the therapists are licensed, their privacy policy, or therapist compensation model, check out this FAQ: https://www.betterhelp.com/your-questions-answered/

Since 1998, there have been over 80 Marvel movies and shows, and ALL OF THEM could come back as references in Deadpool & Wolverine. The MCU, the Fox X-Men franchise, the Blade trilogy, the Sam Raimi Spider-Man trilogy, the Fantastic Four films, the Daredevil films, the Netflix Marvel series, Agents of SHIELD… it’s all too much to catch up on, so which of them do we NEED to rewatch and know about before watching Deadpool & Wolverine? Erik Voss gives a complete recap / primer / explanation of the full history of Marvel in film, from the early days of Blade in 1998 and Kevin Feige meeting Hugh Jackman while working on X-Men (2000). Included at the end of this recap: a CHEAT SHEET of the THREE MOVIES you must make time to rewatch before going into Deadpool & Wolverine (2024).

snippet.title: Why EV Leases Are So Cheap Right Now In The U.S.
snippet.description:
Automakers are offering steep discounts on electric vehicles, and especially on leases. In the first three months of 2024, less than a quarter of car buyers leased vehicles, but more than a third of EV buyers did. By May, nearly 70% of customers getting EVs through dealerships were leased. But EV leasing is problematic for carmakers. While the discounts suggest automakers could be offsetting losses in their EV businesses, the resale values are especially low for them.

snippet.title: Project 2025: The Radical Conservative Plan to Reshape America Under Trump | WSJ
snippet.description:
The Heritage Foundation’s Project 2025 is a radical blueprint for a future Republican administration. Former president Donald Trump has distanced himself from the plan, but Democrats aren’t buying Trump’s rebuke. If enacted, this 920-page document would usher in the most conservative executive branch in modern American history.

WSJ takes an inside look at Project 2025’s most controversial policy proposals and how it could transform the American government.

Chapters:
0:00 Project 2025
0:50 Key principles
2:12 Plans for dismantling the “administrative state”
5:51 Implementing Project 2025
8:50 Pushback

News Explainers
Some days the high-speed news cycle can bring more questions than answers. WSJ’s news explainers break down the day's biggest stories into bite-size pieces to help you make sense of the news.

snippet.title: Charlie Sykes: GOP “Absolutely Confident” That They Will Win in 2024 | Amanpour and Company
snippet.description:
The Republican National Convention begins next week in Wisconsin. In many ways, the battleground state reflects the recent history of the GOP, with Republicans swinging more and more to the right, ending in a full-on embrace of Donald Trump’s MAGA policies. A close observer of this phenomenon is Charlie Sykes, founder of The Bulwark and a respected voice amongst never-Trump Republicans. Sykes joined Walter Isaacson to analyze what cards Republicans might play in the upcoming election, and what strategies Biden might adopt, post-debate.

Originally aired on July 12, 2024
